HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 399
BY REPRESENTATIVE MCMAKIN
COMMENDATIONS: Commends the Louisiana Blazers Elite youth softball team on
winning the 2026 USA Softball 16u National Championship
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend the Louisiana Blazers Elite youth softball team on winning the 2026 USA
3 Softball 16u National Championship.
4 WHEREAS, Louisiana Blazers Elite is a youth softball organization that coaches
5 young women to play high-level softball; the organization begins at 8u and has teams up to
6 18u Amateur; the 16u and 18u teams focus primarily on team and individual player
7 development while also improving players who strive to play in college; and
8 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite 16u team competed in Oklahoma City
9 during the summer of 2025; the team played at Devon Park, the home of the Women's
10 College World Series, and brought home the USA Softball 16u National Championship; and
11 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite 16u team is the first Louisiana team to win
12 the tournament in any age group; the team was undefeated in eleven games, scored fifty-
13 eight runs, and allowed only eight runs; the team shutout its opponents in the quarterfinals,
14 semifinals, and championship games; and
15 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Blazers Elite youth softball team is coached by Will
16 Spencer, JC Fressina, and Logan Lewis; and
17 WHEREAS, the members of the Louisiana Blazers Elite are Jeanne Janise, Harper
18 Fresina, Riley Williams, Kodi Ricks, McKenzie Creel, Riley Perilloux, Bailey Spencer,
19 Bailey Ducote, Avery Hastings, A K Phillips, Rae'El Wheat, Karli Williams, and Aubrey
20 Gaudet; and
